sourcesContent: import React, { Component } from "react"; import { TrainingContainer, TrainingContent, TrainingProgramName, TrainingHeader, Program, TrainingIcon, TrainingDescription, } from "./TrainingStyles"; export default class Training extends Component { render() { return ( Training Platform by Per Scholas Java Full-Stack Web Developer Training covered exploration on how to be efficient in Agile-Scrum project methodologies using Jira. Managed databases requiring SQL and learned how to install, configure, connect, query with MariaDB. Additional topics included collections, basic I/O, JDBC, JPA, and Spring MVC This program requires work in teams and independently to build functioning sites that solve real- world business problems. General Assembly Web Development Immersive Full Stack web development program focusing on ES6 JavaScript, Bootstrap, JSON, jQuery, HTML5, CSS3, Ruby, Rails, Node, Express, Ember, React.js, MongoDB, Postgress, SQL, GIT, problem-solving, planning, modeling, and maintaining applications with client-API architectures, as well as software engineering principles including design patterns, sorting algorithms, big O notation, recursion, and data structures from linked lists to binary trees. This program requires work in teams and independently to build functioning sites that solve real- world business problems. ); } }
